Step 1. Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Total Liabilities (debt): The balance sheet shows only current liabilities of 727,140.68 and no non-current liabilities.  
• Owner's Equity: 28,405,999.64  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = 727,140.68 / 28,405,999.64 ≈ 0.0256, which rounds to 0.03.

Step 2. Net Profit Margin  
• Net Profit (from the income statement): 405,999.64  
• Total Revenue: 14,542,813.42  
• Net Profit Margin = (405,999.64 / 14,542,813.42) × 100 ≈ 2.79%

Step 3. Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• Operating Cash Flow = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities: –17,417,367.15  
• Current Liabilities: 727,140.68  
• Ratio = (–17,417,367.15 / 727,140.68) ≈ –23.95

Thus, the final answer is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.03", 
    "Net Profit Margin": "2.79%", 
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-23.95"
  }
}
